HEADWORD: Hindustani
<hw>Hin"du*sta"ni</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Hind.
<ets>Hind⟦umac⟧st⟦amac⟧n⟦imac⟧</ets> an Indian, fr. Hind. and Per.
<ets>Hind⟦umac⟧st⟦amac⟧n</ets> India.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to
the Hindoos or their language.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The
language of Hindustan; the name given by Europeans to the most generally
spoken of the modern Aryan languages of India. It is Hindi with the
addition of Persian and Arabic words.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
